des:
Link to the Pixbee SmartLife app so you can use your voice to control your Pixbee smart home devices. If you encounter any problems, please contact us at support.pixbee.com.au/support/home.

CONTROL EXAMPLE:
You can simply ask Alexa to control your Pixbee smart products with Voice after connecting Alexa to the products in a few simple steps:
(1) Download our “Pixbee SmartLife” app in Google Play or iOS App Store;
(2) Launch the “Pixbee SmartLife” app and register a new account (or login if you’re already registered);
(3) Turn on your Pixbee smart products and connect them with the “Pixbee SmartLife” app. Please refer to your product manual for detailed instructions.
(4) IMPORTANT: You can rename your smart product with the “Pixbee SmartLife” app. For instance, you can rename your Pixbee Smart Sleep Helper resti as “resti”. Once renamed, the product will be discovered as “resti” in Step 9;
(5) Download the Amazon "Alexa" app from Amazon Market, Google Play or iOS App Store. Launch the “Alexa” app and register a new account (or login if you’re already registered);
(6) Search the Alexa Skills directory for “Pixbee SmartLife”;
(7) Click and Enable skill of “Pixbee SmartLife”, you'll be navigated to the login page, follow the instructions on the page to complete linking;
(8) Talk to Alexa “Alexa, discover devices.” and wait till she says “Discover is completed”;
(9) Now all setup is finished. Try talk to Alexa to control your newly discovered smart product:
“Alexa, turn on resti.”
“Alexa, turn off resti.”
“Alexa, set/make resti to (1-100) percent.”
“Alexa, set/make resti to (colour).”
"Alexa, set the volume of resti to (1-100)."
